On the whole, this date can be regarded in no other light than as the ,hasty conclusion of some unknown per- son, who finding a series of rolls commencing with the Second year of the reign of one of our Kings, and an unappropriated roll beside, concluded that this must be the roll that was required to make the series of that reign complete.

When the attention of the Antiquaries of England began to be directed on this document as one of the sources of historical knowledge, the error of the office-date was soon discovered, and the roll itself is now made to protest against it.
